2500|$|Worker bees {{cooperate}} to {{find food}} {{and use a}} pattern of [...] "dancing" [...] (known as the bee dance or <b>waggle</b> dance) to communicate information regarding resources with each other; this dance varies from species to species, but all living species of Apis exhibit some form of the behavior. If the resources {{are very close to}} the hive, they may also exhibit a less specific dance commonly known as the [...] "round dance".|$|E
